metadata.name: Shine On #235
metadata.description:
You enter a room, bathed in light
Where a beautiful sculpture takes your sight
Shimmering in the glow of the sun
It's a sight to behold, it's simply won

Remember when you were young
You shone like the sun
Your radiance filled the room
With a feeling of pure bloom

Your heart sings, a soul takes flight
As you stand in awe, all worries take flight
Shine on you crazy diamond, bright and true
Your radiance fills the room, your heart anew

metadata.name: pantonX.3 #172
metadata.description:
pantonX.3
is the third drop of the zukuNFT project, which is dedicated to geometric and minimalist standards of early geometric art.
inspired by the "bauhaus grundkurs" based on the didactic concepts of the bauhaus (1919-1933) and its teachings by johannes itten, paul klee, wassily kandinsky, lászló moholy-nagy and josef albers. the preliminary courses and their basic design tasks dealt syntactically with circle, line and square as well as color, and contrasts.

i am a visual artist and have worked in the field of coding since the early years of processing.
always loved geometric and minimalist art, bauhaus, de stijl, piet mondrian, sol leWitt -- just to name a few -- and last but not least verner panton, have had a influence on my artistic work.

library: p5js
"s" key for saving

bauhaus small writing

www.e-art.co

metadata.description:
Unexpressed words, lines, emotions.
where will they go?
set them free,
make art.

created by @mdollinger with p5js and chroma-js

20 custom palettes.
5 resolutions.

Press S to save a png file
Press T to save a tiff file

other libraries: canvas-to-tiff

metadata.name: A Distant Memory #7
metadata.description:
A distant memory of trees, buildings and the old village. Once a moment, the memory is illuminated by a beam of light, which gives me the insight of this work.

--------------------

This is an abstract generation made by pure code.

--------------------

In live mode, press 's' or 'S' to save a high resolution png.

Please be patient with drawing process (it'll take one minute in my computer).
This is my last artwork in 2022. I hope you like this work.

Endlessworld 2022

metadata.name: Archiplex II #29
metadata.description: Archiplex II lays its foundations on Brutalist and Bauhaus design. Through simple, triangular shapes and hand-picked, bold colour palettes, this long-form series explores how generative methods can play and meld with these traditional architectural and design forms.
